nodes.name: RV 1.1
nodes.text: Hymn to Agni, the divine fire. We invoke you as messenger between gods and men.

nodes.name: RV 1.2
nodes.text: Praise to Vayu, the wind god. Come swiftly with your team of steeds to our sacrifice.

nodes.name: RV 1.3
nodes.text: Ashvins, the divine twins, we call you healers. Bring your golden chariot to aid us.

nodes.name: RV 1.4
nodes.text: Indra, wielder of the thunderbolt, destroyer of forts, drink Soma and grant us strength.

nodes.name: RV 1.5
nodes.text: Varuna, lord of cosmic order, may we be sinless before your all-seeing gaze.

nodes.name: RV 1.6
nodes.text: Surya, the radiant sun, you rise daily bringing light to the world of mortals.

nodes.name: RV 1.7
nodes.text: Ushas, the dawn goddess, your rosy fingers chase away the darkness of night.

nodes.name: RV 1.8
nodes.text: Soma, pressed by stones, flows golden like nectar, granting immortality to gods.

nodes.name: RV 1.9
nodes.text: Maruts, storm gods with shining spears, your thunder brings life-giving rain.

nodes.name: RV 1.10
nodes.text: Rudra, fierce yet healing, spare us from your wrath and grant remedies.

nodes.name: RV 1.11
nodes.text: Vishvedevas, all gods together, accept our offerings and grant prosperity.

nodes.name: RV 1.12
nodes.text: Praise for Mitra and Varuna, guardians of truth who uphold divine law.

nodes.name: RV 1.13
nodes.text: Invocation to the divine Hotar priest who perfectly performs the sacrifice.

nodes.name: RV 1.14
nodes.text: Hymn to the sacred fire altar, the navel of the earth where gods descend.

nodes.name: RV 1.15
nodes.text: Call to the Rbhus, divine craftsmen who fashioned the chariot of the gods.

nodes.name: RV 1.16
nodes.text: Indra's might is praised, how he slew Vritra and released the pent-up waters.

nodes.name: RV 1.17
nodes.text: Agni as witness to truth, the god who knows all deeds, both good and evil.

nodes.name: RV 1.18
nodes.text: Dawn and Night, sisters who alternate, bringers of light and rest to mortals.

nodes.name: RV 1.19
nodes.text: Apam Napat, child of waters, shining golden in the rivers' depths.

nodes.name: RV 1.20
nodes.text: To the divine doors of morning, through which the sun's radiance emerges.

nodes.name: RV 1.21
nodes.text: Agni as the messenger, swift runner between earth and heaven.

nodes.name: RV 1.22
nodes.text: Praise for the Adityas, celestial gods who uphold cosmic order.

nodes.name: RV 1.23
nodes.text: To the divine weapons, Indra's thunderbolt and Agni's flaming spear.

nodes.name: RV 1.24
nodes.text: Varuna's wisdom extolled, how he measures the earth and sky with precision.

nodes.name: RV 1.25
nodes.text: The sacred Soma plant, pressed between stones, yields its intoxicating juice.

nodes.name: RV 1.26
nodes.text: Praise for the divine chariot that carries the gods to the sacrifice.

nodes.name: RV 1.27
nodes.text: Indra's heroic deeds recalled, how he won the cosmic battle for gods.

nodes.name: RV 1.28
nodes.text: To the divine cow, mother of plenty, whose milk nourishes all beings.

nodes.name: RV 1.29
nodes.text: The cosmic waters praised, source of all creation and sustenance.

nodes.name: RV 1.30
nodes.text: Hymn to the divine horse, swift as thought, carrying prayers to the gods.

nodes.name: RV 1.31
nodes.text: Praise for the divine craftsman Tvastar, who fashioned Indra's thunderbolt.

nodes.name: RV 1.32
nodes.text: The cosmic tree described, whose roots are above and branches below.

nodes.name: RV 1.33
nodes.text: Indra's strength celebrated, how he supports both heaven and earth.

nodes.name: RV 1.34
nodes.text: To the divine falcon who brings Soma from the highest heaven.

nodes.name: RV 1.35
nodes.text: The sacred fire sticks praised, whose friction births Agni anew each day.

nodes.name: RV 1.36
nodes.text: Hymn to the divine months and seasons, the orderly progression of time.

nodes.name: RV 1.37
nodes.text: The celestial rivers praised, flowing with honey and immortal waters.

nodes.name: RV 1.38
nodes.text: To the divine eagle, messenger between realms, bearer of ambrosia.

nodes.name: RV 1.39
nodes.text: Praise for the divine plow that tills the earth and brings forth abundance.

nodes.name: RV 1.40
nodes.text: The sacred word celebrated, vibration that creates and sustains the cosmos.

nodes.name: RV 1.41
nodes.text: Hymn to the divine light that dispels ignorance and reveals truth.

nodes.name: RV 1.42
nodes.text: The cosmic sacrifice described, where gods offered Purusha to create world.

nodes.name: RV 1.43
nodes.text: Praise for the divine cowherd who protects and multiplies the herds.

nodes.name: RV 1.44
nodes.text: To the divine weaver who crafts the fabric of the universe with skill.

nodes.name: RV 1.45
nodes.text: The sacred breath praised, prana that animates all living beings.

nodes.name: RV 1.46
nodes.text: Hymn to the divine architect who built the mansions of the gods.

nodes.name: RV 1.47
nodes.text: The celestial music celebrated, rhythms that maintain cosmic order.

nodes.name: RV 1.48
nodes.text: Praise for the divine physician who heals both body and spirit.

nodes.name: RV 1.49
nodes.text: To the divine judge who weighs deeds with perfect justice.

nodes.name: RV 1.50
nodes.text: The golden sun praised, whose chariot crosses the sky each day.

nodes.name: RV 1.51
nodes.text: Hymn to the divine warrior who protects the righteous in battle.
